comments: Horford (BOS) establishes himself in Vincent's (MIA) path before the contact and they engage and disengage during the pick.
Tatum (BOS) and Vincent (MIA) come together and then disengage.
Adebayo (MIA) jumps vertically and absorbs the contact that occurs during Tatum's (BOS) driving shot attempt.
Robison (MIA) boxes Horford (BOS) out under the rim and Horford (BOS) trips over Butler (MIA), who is in a legal guarding position.
Tatum (BOS) jumps across Butler's (MIA) path and makes contact with his front and right arm, which impacts the driving shot attempt at the basket.
Martin (MIA) and Brown (BOS) briefly engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity, and the contact is marginal.
Horford (BOS) and Martin (MIA) momentarily entangle their arms during the rebounding opportunity, and the marginal contact dissolves shortly thereafter.
Martin (MIA) gathers the ball on his left foot after he comes down, and uses his right foot to pivot.
Butler (MIA) momentarily has his hand on the ball before Smart (BOS) pulls away.
Tatum (BOS) establishes a screening position to Robinson's (MIA) side before the contact.
Butler (MIA) legally contests Tatum's (BOS) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Robinson (MIA) initiates contact with Brown's (BOS) head, which affects the layup attempt at the basket.
Martin (MIA) steps into the lane prior to Brown (BOS) releasing his free throw attempt, preventing White (BOS) from getting into position to rebound.
Adebayo (MIA) and Smart (BOS) engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity.
Horford (BOS) initiates contact to Butler (MIA) that affects driving shot attempt.
Brown (BOS) and Martin (MIA) mutually engage while the shot is in the air.
Brown (BOS) establishes himself in Vincent's (MIA) path before the contact.
Butler (MIA) reaches for the ball, making marginal contact with Tatum (BOS).
Vincent (MIA) moves laterally and turns into Tatum's (BOS) path after his gather, initiating body contact that affects Tatum's driving shot attempt.
Robinson (MIA) and Smart (BOS) engage under the rim as the ball falls to Tatum (BOS).
Tatum (BOS) legally recovers the ball after Smart (BOS) makes contact with it.
Adebayo (MIA) cleanly blocks Tatum's (BOS) layup attempt at the basket.
Brown (BOS) legally contests Robinson's (MIA) perimeter jump shot  attempt.
Martin (MIA) makes marginal contact with Tatum (BOS) when reaching for the ball during the rebound.
Robinson (MIA) commits a take foul on Smart (BOS). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of the fourth quarter or overtime.
Horford (BOS) initiates brief contact to Adebayo (MIA) without affecting his SQBR.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes a screening position in Tatum's (BOS) path before the contact.
Butler (MIA) fumbles the ball out of his control when he ends his dribble, then recovers it and legally attempts a field goal.

Replay review of the foul called on Horford (BOS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Horford (BOS) made contact with Butler (MIA) during his shooting motion and a foul was warranted.  During the review, the Replay Center Official also determined that i) the foul occurred at 3.0 seconds and adjusted the clock accordingly; and ii) Butler's shot attempt was taken from behind the three-point line, and therefore three free throws were awarded.
Smart (BOS) establishes himself in Adebayo's (MIA) path before the contact.
Vincent (MIA) legally contests Smart's (BOS) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Strus (MIA) legally contests White's (BOS) put-back layup attempt. The shot is released prior to the expiration of the game clock.
